<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 3:36AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog this Morning...
Patchy dense fog has developed across much of southeast Tennessee
and southwest North Carolina, including the Sequatchie valley. The
fog may reduce visibility to one-quarter mile or less. When
traveling this morning drive with caution and slow down. Be
prepared for sudden drop in visibility due to the fog. Give
yourself extra room between you and the vehicle ahead of you.
The fog will dissipate by mid-morning giving way to partly cloudy
sky. Scattered thunderstorms are expected this afternoon.</description>
